2.0 Using the Internet

This guide was designed with the assumption that most people 
using it will have a minimal familiarity with the Internet, 
the way it works, and how to begin navigating it.  If this 
is not the case (read: "if you don't know what we're talking 
about") we highly recommend reading up on the Internet.  
What we would recommend is Ed Krol's "The Whole Internet:  
User's Guide and Catalog."  This book offers very easy to 
understand instructions on how to use and navigate the 
Internet, and why it works.  We found it to be absolutely 
indispensable in the creation of this guide.

